					<head>Midrash</head>
					<msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85085046" rend="visible">
						<summary>Nur al-tsulm, an Arabic-Hebrew midrashic commentary on the Pentateuch by Nathanael ben Isaiah. </summary>
						<textLang mainLang="he" otherLangs="ara"/>
						<msItem n="0" rend="visible" class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85085046">
							<locus from="1r" to="130v"/>
							<title xml:lang="ara-Latn-x-lc">Nur al-tzulm </title>
							<title xml:lang="jrb">נור אלצלם</title>
							<author>
								<persName xml:lang="en">Nathanael ben Isaiah </persName>
								<persName xml:lang="he">נתנאל בן ישעיהו</persName>
							</author>
							<listBibl>
								<bibl>
									<ref target="Kohut_1894"/>
								</bibl>
							</listBibl>
							<filiation>Cf. Or 2356, <ref target="Margoliouth_1965" type="number">360</ref>. </filiation>
							<msItem rend="v">
								<locus from="1r" to="21v"/>
								<title xml:lang="en">Midrash on Genesis</title>
								<note>
									<p>Contains two small fragments of the commentary on Genesis: from Lekh lekha to Ṿa-yera and from Toledot to Ṿa-yishlaḥ.</p>
									<p>Both parts include the same poetic piece, provided with the superlinear punctuation and decorated with coloured designs.</p>
								</note>
							</msItem>
							<msItem rend="v">
								<locus from="22r" to="130v"/>
								<title xml:lang="en">Midrash on the Pentateuch</title>
								<note>
									<p>A large naumber of fragments containing portions of the whole work.</p>
									<p>Exodus begins on folio 61r-73r; Leviticus - 73r-102v; Numbers - 102v-130v. </p>
									<p>Breaks off with parashah Maṭot. </p>
								</note>
							</msItem>
						</msItem>
					</msContents>
					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Paper codex; two Yemenite square and semi-cursive script of 14th and 15th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="chart">
								<support>Paper codex. </support>
								<extent>130 folios<dimensions type="leaf" unit="mm">
										<height>235</height>
